Privacy Policy for WizDex
Effective Date: 20/08/2024

1. Introduction
WizDex ("the App") is a mobile application designed to provide users with detailed information about Pokémon, including their types, stats, moves, and evolution chains. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our App. Please read this policy carefully to understand our views and practices regarding your personal data and how we will treat it.

2. Information We Collect
We do not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) from users. The App is designed to function without requiring users to submit personal information.
2.1 Automatically Collected Information
- Usage Data: We may collect non-personal, anonymous information related to the usage of the App, such as app interactions, usage frequency, and error reports. This data is used solely to improve the functionality and user experience of the App.
- Device Information: We may collect information about your device, such as the type of mobile device you use, your device's unique ID, the IP address of your device, your operating system, and information about the way you use the App.

3. How We Use Information
The information we collect is used to:
- Improve the performance and usability of the App.
- Analyze trends and usage patterns to enhance user experience.
- Resolve issues and respond to user feedback.

4. Third-Party Services
WizDex does not share your personal information with third parties. However, the App may use third-party services, such as analytics tools, which may collect and use information as described in their privacy policies. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services you interact with through the App.

5. Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected through the App. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Children's Privacy
WizDex is not directed toward individuals under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under 13, please contact us immediately, and we will take steps to delete such information.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the "Effective Date" at the top will be updated accordingly. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.

8. Fair Use Policy
This app uses PokéAPI for sourcing all the information. PokéAPI is free and open to use. It is also very popular. Because of this, we ask every developer to abide by our fair use policy. People not complying with the fair use policy will have their IP address permanently banned.
PokéAPI is primarily an educational tool, and we will not tolerate denial of service attacks preventing people from learning.

9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:
virtualwiz401@gmail.com
